The bank said it did not know about traces of tallow, which contains animal fats, in the production of the currency when it signed the contract with Innovia. We are aware of some people s concerns in our new note. We respect those concerns and are treating them with the utmost seriousness, the bank said in a statement. Read also:&nbsp;Dealing with slippery cashEarlier, the Bank of England confirmed that tallow is used in the production of the new currency, after an online petition against its use in the notes was signed by more 100 000 supporters in less than two daysREUTERS